----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Level 1 - Basic Transposition - Reverse Cipher

The reverse cipher is a very simple and weak method of encryption.  Each letter is simply put in reverse order.
In order to progress you must decrypt the following message:
Cipher text: hguorht ees nac uoy gnihtemos
Plain text: something you can see through
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Level 2 - Transposition - Rail Fence Cipher

A transposition cipher works by moving and rearraning letters.  The rail fence cipher etc etc
[img]example image[/img]
In order to progress you must decrypt the following message:
Cipher text: IYUIEEAEIILIFOGVMWTRWLDE
Plain text: If you give me water I will die
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Level 3 - Substitution - Caesar Cipher

The caesar cipher is a substitution cipher which works by shifting
[img]example image[/img]
In order to progress you must decrypt the following message:
Cipher text: Vdb pb qdph dqg L glvdsshdu
Plain text: Say my name and I disappear
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Level 4 - Substitution Cipher 

A subsitution cipher replaces the plain text letters with another set of letters or symbols.
[img]example image[/img]
In order to progress you must decrypt the following message:
Cipher text: a kiiy oxfn ji liiku ik oxjliou
Plain text:  A room with no doors or windows
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
